## Named constants — tunables for monetization

All in `js/hunt/hunt-turret.js`. Read via `WG.HuntTurret.TUNABLES` (frozen).

### Turret combat
- `TURRET_FIRE_RATE       = 1.4`     seconds between shots
- `TURRET_RANGE           = 200`     world units — target acquisition radius
- `TURRET_DAMAGE          = 12`      per projectile
- `TURRET_PROJ_SPEED      = 360`     world units / sec
- `TURRET_PROJ_LIFE       = 1.4`     seconds (range/speed ≈ 0.55s; margin)
- `TURRET_AIM_LERP        = 0.18`    smoothing factor toward desired angle
- `TURRET_AIM_FIRE_THRESH = 0.35`    radians — fire only when aim within this
- `TURRET_BARREL_LEN      = 14`      muzzle offset along aim direction (world units)
- `TURRET_PROJ_COLOR      = '#ffe48a'`

### Turret durability
- `TURRET_MAX_HP          = 80`
- `TURRET_HIT_RANGE       = 14`      enemy attacks turret if within this distance

### Campfire
- `CAMPFIRE_REGEN_RADIUS  = 60`
- `CAMPFIRE_REGEN_RATE    = 4`       hp / sec while inside
- `CAMPFIRE_SPARKLE_PERIOD= 0.16`    seconds between green-sparkle emissions

## Architect-mandated polish (POLISHED PRODUCT)

- **Eased lerp aim tracking** — shortest-path angle lerp at 0.18/tick. Cannon barrel reads `c.aimAngle` (was a fake sine animation) so the visual matches what the targeting logic actually thinks.
- **Aim-tolerance fire gate** — turrets only fire when aim is within 0.35 rad of target, so a cannon spinning to acquire a side-target doesn't loose a 90°-off shot. Once gated, fireTimer is held at 0 so the next shot pops the moment aim catches up — feels responsive on fast-moving targets.
- **Muzzle flash** — `muzzleFlash` particle type (5 yellow/orange particles, 0.18s, sMin 90 sMax 160). Fires at the muzzle tip on every `turret:fire` event.
- **Projectile trail + glow halo** — projectiles get a `_trail: []` array; `drawProjectiles` populates 8 samples per frame + draws a fading streak (alpha + width grow toward the head) + a radial-gradient glow halo at the head. Reads as "moving fast" not "drifting dot."
- **Animated turret HP bar** — `_hpDisplayed` is lerped from `hp` at rate dt*8 in `tickOne`, rendered with hue shift green→yellow→red. Damage reads as a smooth sweep, not a snap. Dark background frame for readability over green tile.
- **Turret destruction explosion** — `turret:destroyed` event triggers `turretExplode` particle burst (18 ring particles, 0.65s, orange→brown). Slot reverts to dashed-circle for rebuild (have=0, built=false).
- **Campfire regen sparkles** — `campfireSparkle` type (1 sparkle per emission, 0.85s life, negative gravity = drift up, green palette) emitted at 6 Hz while player regenerating. Cumulative density reads as a healing aura.
- **Faint pulsing regen ring on the ground** — dashed green-white ring at every built campfire. Brightness + line width step up when player is inside the radius (visual confirmation that regen is active). Reads radius from `HuntTurret.TUNABLES` (single source of truth).

## Edge cases handled inline

- Turret HP/aim/fireTimer fields lazy-initialised on first tick (so a stage that mutates `props.constructions` outside the build flow still gets correct fields on next tick).
- Rebuild after destruction → `_resetOnRebuild` restores HP fields fresh when `built` flips from false→true with `hp <= 0`.
- Aim wraparound at ±π handled by `lerpAngle` shortest-path math — no spinning the long way around when target crosses behind the turret.
- No targets in range → cannon drifts gently back toward up (lerp factor * 0.25), doesn't freeze pointing wherever the last enemy died.
- Player not in stage → tick early-returns via runtime/player guards.
- Ranged enemies (Caller) ignore turrets — they keep firing at the player from range. Turrets don't tank ranged.
- Enemy turret-attack range adds `c.size/2` so a Brute (size 24) engages from a sensible standoff instead of overlapping the wagon sprite.
- Sparkle accumulator resets to 0 the moment player leaves regen radius — no carry-over emit on re-entry.

## Verification (live browser smoke test, port 3996)

- Stage 1 day mode entered, all 4 turrets and the campfire force-built, 3 walkers spawned 60–100 units from a turret. Sim ticked 80 frames @ dt=0.05 (4s).
- **11 turret-damage events fired**, **1 turret destroyed** — slot correctly reappeared as a dashed "Turret 0/4" build circle (rebuildable).
- HP bar **lerped smoothly** — captured `_hpDisplayed = 6.0` mid-decay while `hp = 0` (post-destruction lerp catching up).
- **Player HP regen verified**: started 40, ended 56 after 4s @ CAMPFIRE_REGEN_RATE=4 = exact match (16 hp gained).
- **Projectile trails captured visually** — yellow streaks visible in flight from active turrets to distant walkers (screenshot at 12 ticks @ 0.05).
- **Animated HP bars visually verified** on damaged turrets — yellow at ~50% hp, green at ~87%.
- **Pulsing dashed regen ring visually verified** around the campfire when player stood on it.
- **No console errors** at any point.

